data.chText: 她像平常一样老老实实地回答了我的所有问题。
data.enText: She answered all my questions with her usual honesty.

data.chText: 他的诚实是毋庸置疑的。
data.enText: His honesty is not in question.
used to state a fact or an opinion which, though true, may seem disappointing

data.chText: 说实话，这本书并没有我预期的那么好。
data.enText: The book isn't, in all honesty, as good as I expected.
used to state a fact or an opinion which, though true, may seem disappointing

data.chText: 说实话，这本书并没有我预期的那么好。
data.enText: The book isn't, in all honesty, as good as I expected.

tr: southeastern European plant cultivated for its fragrant purplish flowers and round flat papery silver-white seedpods that are used for indoor decoration

value.def: Honesty is the quality of being honest.

example.ex: They said the greatest virtues in a politician were integrity, correctness and honesty.
example.tran: 他们说政治家身上最重要的美德就是正直、得体和诚实。

defx.def: You say in all honesty when you are saying something that might be disappointing or upsetting, and you want to soften its effect by emphasizing your sincerity.

example.ex: In all honesty, aren't there already far too many pages of scientific research published every week?...
example.tran: 说实话，不是已经每周都有连篇累牍的科学研究论文发表了吗？

example.ex: But in all honesty, I wish it had never happened.
example.tran: 但是老实说，我希望这事从未发生过。

value.def: Honesty is a plant whose seeds are contained in silvery-white papery discs.
